article.headline: San Diego 77, Siena 60
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Johnny Dee scored 27 points and made four 3-pointers to lead San Diego to a 77-60 victory against Siena in a NUCDF Basketball Challenge contest on Sunday. Ken Rancifer added 13 points and Cameron Miles 10 for the Toreros (3-2). O.D. Anosike had 19 points and 13 rebounds and Rob Poole scored 12 points for the Saints (2-3). Siena trailed 42-30 at halftime and was within striking distance with five minutes remaining, down nine. But buckets by Rancifer, Miles and Chris Anderson and two free throws by Dee comprised an 8-1 run that made the score 75-59 with 2:13 remaining.
